{
  "name": "Ricocheting Weapon",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/commodities/tech/tube-chamber-lightning.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Prerequisite: Thrown Weapon (consumed on creation)</p><p>Cost: 8 Creation Points</p><p>Drain: 10 CCD Chakra</p><p></p><p>You create a ranged weapon engineered to ricochet of its targets You have proficiency in this weapon, and it has the Finesse, Thrown (30/90), and Special properties, and deals 2d8 bludgeoning, piercing or slashing damage (chosen at the time you select this upgrade). </p><p>You do not add any modifiers to any damage rolls with this weapon. </p><p>Special: When this weapon is thrown you can spend the CCD Chakra Drain target two creatures within 20 ft of the original target, making a separate attack roll against each target. </p><p>You can add your Intelligence modifier to damage rolls while it is ricocheting. </p><p>The weapon shatters after the third attack roll and you regain the Creation Points Spent.</p>",
